Interpretation: This provision establishes a conditional cross-border data transfer regime. It prohibits transfers outside Malaysia unless the destination ensures an adequate level of protection (as determined by the Minister) or specific exceptions apply, such as the data subject's consent, contractual necessity, or the data user exercising due diligence to ensure the data is not processed in a way that would contravene the Act.
